# Torres Vistoria — Cursor Rules

## Stack
- React 19 + TypeScript (strict)
- Vite 6 + TailwindCSS 4
- shadcn/ui + Radix UI
- React Query v5 + Zustand
- React Hook Form + Zod
- Supabase (Auth, DB, Storage)
- Recharts + pdfmake + ExcelJS

## Code Style
- Named exports ONLY (no default exports)
- Absolute imports with `@/` prefix
- Functional components + hooks
- TypeScript strict mode (no `any`)
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- Components < 150 lines (extract logic to hooks)
- JSDoc for complex functions
- const/let, never var

## Patterns
- **Auth:** React Context (`auth-context`) + `auth-service` — não duplicar em Zustand persist
- **Server state:** React Query (hooks + services)
- **Client UI state:** Zustand (`ui-store`, `inspection-store` para drafts)
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Loading states and error boundaries
- Toasts via `useToast()` + `ToastViewport` em `AppProviders`

## Security
- RLS policies on ALL tables
- Zod validation on ALL inputs
- Never commit secrets — use `.env.local`
- Role/company in `app_metadata` (never `user_metadata` in RLS)

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`VistoriaCard`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use-` prefix (`useInspections`)
- Services: kebab-case with `-service` suffix (`inspection-service`)
- Schemas: camelCase (`vistoriaSchema`)
- Files: kebab-case

## Supabase
- Use MCP Supabase for migrations, types and advisors
- Validate with `get_advisors` after DDL

## Layout
- `AppShell` compõe `Header`, `Sidebar`, `MobileNav`, `MobileDrawer`
- Nav items centralizados em `src/lib/nav-items.ts`

## Ordem de implementação
Roadmap Fase 1: Auth → Dashboard → Vistorias → Fotos → Checklist → PDF → Financeiro → Deploy
